                    "name": "Create Object",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "<b>Frequency</b> three times per day; <b>Effect</b> The leprechaun produces an item out of their hat, from behind their jacket, from within a hole in a tree stump, or from any other unexpected location. This conjured item must be no more than 1 Bulk and must be made of relatively commonplace material (such as cloth, wood, stone, or even low-value metal like iron or lead). It can't rely on intricate artistry or complex moving parts, never fulfills a Cost or the like, and can't be made of precious materials or materials with a rarity of <a aonid=\"159\" game-obj=\"Traits\">uncommon</a> or higher. The created object is temporary and lasts for 1 hour or until the leprechaun creates a new item, whichever comes first.",
